Connector types and icons - Developer
Skip to content
Connector types and icons
¶
Following are all the available connector types (including their icons) for assets in Atlan.
These determine the icons used for assets in Atlan
The value you set for the connector determines the icons you will see for all assets contained within that connection in Atlan.
CustomEntity
assets? Define custom connector types dynamically
If you're working with
CustomEntity
assets, the connector type may vary depending on the user — it could be any valid string. To support this, we've added a way to dynamically extend the
AtlanConnectorType
enum in the SDK. This enables support for custom connectors without needing changes to the core SDK.
For example, to create a new custom connector called
"my-custom"
:

Use
AtlanConnectorType.CREATE_CUSTOM()
to define your custom connector. Provide:
name
: Enum-style name to use in your code (eg:
MY_CUSTOM
)
value
: Actual string sent in API calls (eg:
my-custom
)
category
: (Optional) Defaults to
AtlanConnectionCategory.CUSTOM
if not provided.
After defining the custom connector, you can refer to it using
AtlanConnectorType.MY_CUSTOM
throughout your script, just like any built-in connector type.
